	"description": "In 2008, the Center for Urban Economic Development surveyed\n[http://nelp.3cdn.net/e470538bfa5a7e7a46_2um6br7o3.pdf] 4,387 low-wage workers\nin Chicago, Los Angeles, and New York City. They wanted to determine the extent\nof violations of employment laws in core sectors of the US economy.\n\nThey discovered that:\n\n * 76% of those who worked more than 40 hours were not paid the legally required\n   overtime rate.\n * 68% of the sample experienced at least one pay-related violation in the\n   previous wor",
