	"keywords": "Open Source, Python, Startup, Web Development, Tech",
	"description": "Github has made it easy for millions of developers to publicize their projects\nso they can attract users and collaborators. But these developers often find\nthemselves spending hundreds of hours building a project, only to push it to\nGitHub and earn a mere one or two stars.\n\nI found myself in this situation while building a project for the nonprofit I\nwork at, Hack4Impact [http://hack4impact.org]. It’s a student group that makes \ntechnical projects [http://hack4impact.org/projects] for community\n",
	"headline": "How we got our 2-year-old repo trending on GitHub in just 48 hours",
